\begin{align*} -2.54 &= \fbox{ -3}+\varepsilon\\ \Rightarrow \lfloor -2.54\rfloor &= \fbox{ -3} \end{align*}

The floor function, denoted by $\lfloor x\rfloor$, is a mathematical operation that returns the greatest integer less than or equal to $x$. In this case, the floor of -2.54 is -3 because -3 is the largest integer that is still less than -2.54.

Next, we find the ceiling of 25.4.
\begin{align*} 25.4&=\fbox{ 25}+\delta \\ \Rightarrow \lceil25.4\rceil &=\fbox{ 26} \end{align*}

The ceiling function, denoted by $\lceil x\rceil$, is the opposite of the floor function. It returns the smallest integer greater than or equal to $x$. In this case, the ceiling of 25.4 is 26 because 26 is the smallest integer that is still greater than 25.4.

Now, we combine our results.
\begin{align*} \lfloor-2.54\rfloor+\lceil25.4\rceil=\fbox{-3} + \fbox{ 26} \end{align*}

\begin{align*} \boxed{\phantom{0}+3}\hspace{.3cm}&\boxed{\phantom{0}=23}\hspace{.3cm}\boxed{\phantom{0}=-3} \end{align*}

The final answer is obtained by adding -3 and 26, which equals 23.

